\section{Acquisition Policy}
\minibib

\subsection{Acquisition-Related Laws and Regulations}
\srcCite{edo-3.3.1-policy-players-2025}

\subsubsection{Title 10 USC}: Governs the organization, structure and operation of the Armed Forces of the United States.
\begin{itemize}
  \item Several sections charge the secretaries of the military departments(Army, Navy, and Air Force) with responsibility to “equip” the armed forces.
  \item General acquisition provisions are spread throughout Title 10.
  \item \ac{ndaa}, also set forth in Title 10, is one of the principal mechanism by which Congress modifies the defense acquisition structure.
\end{itemize}

\subsubsection{Other Applicable Laws}
\begin{itemize}
  \item Armed Services Procurement Act (1947), as amended
  \item Small Business Act (1963), as amended
  \item Office of Federal Procurement Policy Act (1983), as amended
  \item Competition in Contracting Act (1984)
  \item DoD Procurement Reform Act (1985)
  \item DoD Reorganization Act of 1986 (Goldwater‐Nichols)
  \item Defense Acquisition Workforce Improvement Act 1990
  \item Federal Acquisition Streamlining Act of 1994
  \item Clinger‐Cohen Act of 1996
  \item Weapon Systems Acquisition Reform Act of 2009
\end{itemize}

\subsubsection{Federal Regulations}
Navy acquisitions is governed by a set of regulations that build on one another.

\paragraph{FAR}~\autocite{FAR}
\begin{itemize}
  \item Primary regulation for use by all Federal agencies for the acquisition of supplies and services with appropriated funds. It is the highest level of regulations for federal acquisitions~\autocite{edo-3.3.1-policy-players-2025}.
  \item Guides and directs \ac{dod} \acp{pm} in:
    \begin{itemize}
      \item Acquisition planning
      \item Competition requirements
      \item Contract award procedures
      \item Warranties
    \end{itemize}
\end{itemize}

\paragraph{DFAR}~\autocite{DFAR}
This is the \ac{dod} Supplement to the \ac{far}. It provides \ac{dod} specific procedures.

\paragraph{DoD Acquisition Policy}.  Articulated in two documents:
\begin{description}
  \item[DoD Directive 5000.01]---The Defense Acquisition System~\autocite{DoDD5000}.  States the policies and principles that guide all defense acquisition programs. Identifies the \ac{dod} key acquisition officials and forums.
  \item[DoD Instruction 5000.02]---Operation of the Adaptive Acquisition Framework~\autocite{DoDI5000-02}. Objective is to deliver effective, suitable, survivable, sustainable, and affordable solutions to the end user in a timely manner. Six pathways provide opportunities for \acp{mda} and \acp{pm} to develop acquisition strategies and employ acquisition processes that match the characteristics of the capability being acquired.
\end{description}
